my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:305:Implement `oscillator.py`. One class that works at every time scale. Parameters: frequency, waveform (sine/saw/triangle/noise/buffer/physical_model), amplitude, envelope (ADSR or arbitrary contour), phase. Modulation inputs: list of other Oscillators that modify this one's frequency, amplitude, or waveform parameters. Output: at audio rate (>20Hz) produces PCM samples (S32_LE, 48kHz). At control rate (0.1-20Hz) produces control values for modulating other oscillators. At form rate (<0.1Hz) produces structural decisions (key change, section boundary, motif selection). Write tests verifying output at multiple time scales, modulation accuracy, and waveform correctness.
